 :tx/rationale "OPEN-LOOP-4: Individual divergence detections returned to caller but not stored as datoms [from AUDIT_REPORT]. signal.rs detect_* functions (detect_confusion, detect_logical, detect_procedural, detect_temporal, etc.) return signal structs to the caller which prints them to stderr. The signals are NOT transacted into the store as signal datoms. This means: (1) no historical record of what divergences were detected, (2) no trend analysis on divergence patterns, (3) no closed loop from detection to resolution. Contrast with braid observe which DOES store observations as datoms. SOLUTION: Each detect_* function should return signal datoms. The caller (or a wrapper) should transact them. Signal entities get :signal/type, :signal/severity, :signal/source, :signal/timestamp attributes. VERIFICATION: After running bilateral scan that detects spec-impl gaps, store contains signal datoms with :signal/type structural. braid query can retrieve signal history. DEPENDENCIES: Prerequisite for AUDIT-COH-5 (signal subscription dispatch). Signals must be stored before they can be subscribed to."
